derivation.yuyuan_name: mid 16th cent. (in the sense 'busy oneself to a particular end, machinate'): alteration of the verb temper

entry.def: If someone tampers with something, they interfere with it or try to change it when they have no right to do so.

example.ex: I don't want to be accused of tampering with the evidence...
example.tran: 我不希望被人控告篡改证据。

example.ex: He found his computer had been tampered with.
example.tran: 他发现他的电脑被人动过手脚。

means.word_mean: 1. a tool for tamping (e.g., for tamping tobacco into a pipe bowl or a charge into a drill hole etc.)
1. play around with or alter or falsify, usually secretively or dishonestly;

sentences.sentence: "Someone tampered with the documents on my desk"

means.word_mean: 2. intrude in other people's affairs or business; interfere unwantedly;
